\hypertarget{circular-velocity}{%
\section{Circular Velocity}\label{circular-velocity}}

The circular velocity \(v_{c}\) is defined via

\[v_{c}\left ( R,z \right ) = \sqrt{R\frac{\partial \Phi \left (R,z  \right )}{\partial R}   }\]

with the total potential being in the presented case

\[\Phi \left ( R,z \right ) = \Phi_{bh} \left ( R,z \right )+\Phi_{disk} \left ( R,z \right )+\Phi_{bulge} \left ( R,z \right )+\Phi_{halo} \left ( R,z \right )\]

therefore

\[v_{c}^{2} = v_{c,bh}^{2}+v_{c,disk}^{2}+v_{c,bulge}^{2}+v_{c,halo}^{2}\]\[v_{c,bh}^{2} = \frac{G M_{bh} R^2}{\left(R^2+z^2\right)^{3/2}}\]\[v_{c,disk}^{2} = \frac{GM_{disk}R^2}{\left(\left(a_{disk}+\sqrt{b_{disk}^2+z^2}\right)^2+R^2\right)^{3/2}}\]\[v_{c,bulge}^{2} = \frac{G M_{bulge} R^2}{\sqrt{R^2+z^2} \left(a_{bulge}+\sqrt{R^2+z^2}\right)^2}\]\[v_{c,halo}^{2} = \frac{4 \pi G \rho _{s} R^2 r_{s}^3 \log \left(\frac{\sqrt{R^2+z^2}}{r_{s}}+1\right)}{\left(R^2+z^2\right)^{3/2}}-\frac{4\pi G\rho_{s} R^2 {r_{s}}^2}{\left(R^2+z^2\right) \left(\frac{\sqrt{R^2+z^2}}{r_{s}}+1\right)}\]

Inserting the parameters given in \texttt{tbl\_parameters} and setting
\(G\approx 4.302*10^{-6}\left [ \frac{kpc}{M_\odot}\frac{km^{2}}{s^{2}} \right ]\)
results in
\(\rho_{s}\approx 4.5*10^{6} \left [ \frac{M_\odot}{kpc^{3}} \right ]\)

the circular velocity can be used for fitting the model parameters
\texttt{Bajkova2017}. \texttt{fig-potential\_circular\_velocity}
displays the velocity for the chosen model and its components.

